-- composition --

the core pattern is functional composition with immutable context:

```js
const workflow = compose(
  scope({ tools: [searchTool], system: "you are a researcher" },
    model({ model: "openai/gpt-4o-mini" })
  ),
  when(toolWasCalled("search"),
    scope({ system: "summarize findings" }, model())
  ),
  tap(ctx => console.log(ctx.lastResponse?.content))
)

const result = await workflow("find info about X")
```

compose() chains steps. scope() isolates context. model() calls the LLM
and auto-executes tool calls. when() branches conditionally. tap() runs
side effects without modifying context.

-- scope inheritance --

scope uses bitwise flags to control what inner steps can see:

Inherit.Nothing (0) - fresh context
Inherit.Conversation (1) - carry message history
Inherit.Tools (2) - carry tool definitions and call counts
Inherit.All (3) - carry everything

default is Inherit.Conversation for most uses. silent scopes execute
tools but don't add to conversation history.

-- providers --

model string format is "provider/model-name":

  model({ model: "openai/gpt-4o-mini" })
  model({ model: "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929" })
  model({ model: "google/gemini-2.0-flash" })

API keys resolved in order: config.apiKey > setKeys() > env vars.
each provider translates messages and tools to its own format internally.

-- tools --

tools are objects with name, description, schema, and execute:

```js
const searchTool = {
  name: "search",
  description: "search the web",
  schema: { query: { type: "string", description: "search query" } },
  execute: async ({ query }) => await search(query),
  _maxCalls: 3,
}
```

tool execution is automatic inside model(). when the LLM returns
tool_calls, model() executes them, adds results to history, and calls
the LLM again until no more tool_calls are returned.

-- approval --

tool approval is opt-in per scope:

```js
scope({
  tools: [dangerousTool],
  toolConfig: {
    requireApproval: true,
    approvalCallback: (call) => confirm(`Allow ${call.function.name}?`)
  }
}, model())
```

also supports event-driven approval for async UIs via
onApprovalRequested/resolveApproval.

-- structured output --

pass a JSON schema or Zod schema to model():

```js
model({
  model: "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  schema: z.object({ name: z.string(), age: z.number() })
})
```

the library normalizes Zod schemas to JSON schema and passes them
to the provider in the appropriate format.

-- threads --

threads provide persistent multi-turn conversations:

```js
const thread = getOrCreateThread("user-123")
await thread.message("hello", compose(model()))
await thread.message("remember what I said?", compose(model()))
```

pluggable storage via ThreadStore interface (get/set). default is
in-memory.

-- streaming --

pass a stream callback to scope or model for real-time output:

```js
scope({ stream: (event) => {
  if (event.type === "content") process.stdout.write(event.content)
  if (event.type === "tool_executing") console.log("calling", event.call.function.name)
}}, model())
```

event types: content, tool_calls_ready, tool_executing, tool_complete,
tool_error, approval_requested, usage.

-- usage tracking --

token usage accumulates through the pipeline:

```js
const result = await workflow("prompt")
console.log(result.usage)
// { promptTokens: 150, completionTokens: 42, totalTokens: 192 }
```

usage propagates through nested scopes, including silent scopes.
each provider extracts usage from its response format.
